{
  "text": "The coupling term can be called the global characteristic matrix of piezoelectricity, while the rest terms retain their previous meaning. The additional remark concerns special or simplified versions of the above equation. The inverse or direct piezoelectric problems can be considered here with the right-hand side terms equal to zero in the first and second equation, respectively. It is also worth mentioning that different pq and πr adaptive approximations of the vectorial displacement and scalar electric fields are proposed in [CITATION_1] , with the common h-approximation.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "121015153"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "121015153": {
      "title": "Application of the three-dimensional triangular-prism hpq adaptive finite element to plate and shell analysis",
      "abstract": "Abstract The paper presents some non-standard information on the algorithm of a three-dimensional hpq triangular-prism finite element as applied in the presented research, including the shape functions definition, definitions of the geometry and displacement field, and a description of the numerical integration. The main part of the paper describes methodology and results of the numerical research on application of the element to plate and shell analysis. It contains justification of three plate and shell examples as well as the results of numerical tests, including such aspects as limits of the solution, locking phenomena, h-, p- and q-convergence, influence of mesh anisotrophy, numerical stability, etc."
    }
  }
}